§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We want a condition for a unique minimizer. ⦉
⦉

§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Suppose $X ⊂ 𝗥$ is convex. ⦉

  ‖ A function $f: X → 𝗥$ is ❬strictly convex❭ if
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(tx + (1-t)y) < tf(x) + (1-t)f(y) ⦉
    ⦉
    for all $t ∈ [0,1]$ and $x,y ∈ X$. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ $f$ is ❬strictly concave❭ if $-f$ is convex. ⦉
⦉

